Program: Find Size of Array using foreach Loop in Java
This Java program demonstrates how to calculate the size of an array using a foreach (enhanced for) loop, without relying on the built-in .length property.

import java.util.*;
public class Foreach_size {

	public static void main(String[] args) {
		// TODO Auto-generated method stub
		int[] arr = {1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6};
		int count = 0;
		for(int num : arr) {
			count++;
		}
		System.out.println(count);
		

	}

}

üîç Description:
Initializes an integer array with predefined values.

Uses a foreach loop to iterate through each element.

Increments a counter during each iteration to determine the array size.

Prints the final size of the array.

üßæ Output:
6
